# Cursor Rules
- Platform: Mac (darwin 24.3.0)
- Shell: /opt/homebrew/bin/zsh

## Command Execution Rules
- Execute commands one at a time
- No command chaining
- Document all command results

## Documentation Rules
- Keep tasks.md as single source of truth
- Update Memory Bank files based on task complexity
- Use creative phases for complex design decisions

## Memory Bank Structure
- projectbrief.md: Core requirements
- productContext.md: Project purpose
- activeContext.md: Current focus
- systemPatterns.md: Architecture
- techContext.md: Tech stack
- progress.md: Status & reflections
- tasks.md: Task tracking 